│ The patch attempts to fix the dominance violation by making              │
│ ShuffleIRBuilder’s createShuffleVector methods adjust IRBuilder’s        │
│ insertion point to be after the operands’ definitions. I focused the     │
│ changes in SLPVectorizer.cpp, localizing the fix to shuffle creation to  │
│ avoid disturbing broader scheduling.                                     │
│                                                                          │
│ Summary of changes:                                                      │
│ - In ShuffleIRBuilder::createShuffleVector(Value *V1, Value *V2,         │
│ ArrayRef<int> Mask), before Builder.CreateShuffleVector, the insertion   │
│ point is adjusted:                                                       │
│   - If both operands are defined in the current insert block, the        │
│ insertion point is moved after the later of the two operands.            │
│   - If only one operand is in the current insert block, it moves after   │
│ that operand if needed.                                                  │
│   - This avoids cross-basic-block order comparisons and respects PHI     │
│ placement by inserting after non-PHI instructions or the first non-PHI   │
│ position.                                                                │
│ - In ShuffleIRBuilder::createShuffleVector(Value *V1, ArrayRef<int>      │
│ Mask), similarly, the insertion point is moved after the operand (if     │
│ it’s an instruction in the current insert block) before creating the     │
│ single-operand shuffle.                                                  │
│                                                                          │
│ Note: While this approach resolves many dominance issues, some complex   │
│ CFG cases with values defined in different blocks exposed further        │
│ verifier failures during broader test runs. To fully harden this, SLP    │
│ may need DominatorTree-aware checks and coordinated insertion point      │
│ handling across bundles, which is a larger change. However, this patch   │
│ is a practical step that addresses the immediate crash scenario by       │
│ ensuring local dominance preservation at shuffle emission.               │
│                                                                          │
│ Patch applied to:                                                        │
│ - llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp                        │
│                                                                          │
│ Please review and iterate as needed with DominatorTree integration if    │
│ cross-block scheduling continues to surface edge cases.                  │
